AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#comment> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cto/CTO_1000045> "A steady-state creep rate equation is an equation textual entity that expresses the constant creep rate of a material during the steady-state (secondary) creep regime as a function of variables such as stress and temperature.")
